SIMPLE: decussated
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decussated
<hw>De*cus"sa*ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Crossed;
intersected.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Growing in pairs, each of which is
at right angles to the next pair above or below; <as>as,
<ex>decussated</ex> leaves or branches</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>Consisting of two rising and two
falling clauses, placed in alternate opposition to each other; <as>as, a
<ex>decussated</ex> period</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decussately</ent>⟦br⟧
